ork includes a focus on personal, organizational and situational factors to predict performance in the role. The study examines the complex nature of the role. These include task complexity, low task visibility, role conflict, and role ambiguity. Personal, organizational and situational factors that can serve as buffers against the complexities associated with the role are presented. The study suggests that individuals with certain competencies and orientations may be better suitable for the ethics position, and firms need to consider key organizational and situational issues critical to the performance of an ethics officer. The research and practice implications of the study are given. Copyright Springer Science+Business Media, Inc. 2006", "ex:volume": "69", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "Exploring the Role Performance of Corporate Ethics Officers", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-006-9068-7", "ex:pages": "57-75", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2006", "ex:keyword": ["Ethics officers", "Ethical leadership", "Ethical infrastructure", "Value-based management", "Technical awareness"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Henry Adobor", "ex:email": "Henry.Adobor@quinnipiac.edu"}]}, {"ex:issue": "4", "ex:volume": "90", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "Global Ethics of Collective Internet Governance: Intrinsic Motivation and Open Source Software", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-009-0057-5", "ex:pages": "523-531", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2009", "ex:keyword": ["Ethics", "Internet governance", "Open source software", "Intrinsic motivation", "Psychological contracts"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Chong Choi"}, {"ex:name": "Sae Kim", "ex:email": "bluelion98@naver.com"}, {"ex:name": "Shui Yu"}]}, {"ex:issue": "3", "ex:volume": "85", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "Toward Dynamic Corporate Stakeholder Responsibility", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-009-0213-y", "ex:pag