e", "Ethical leadership", "Business ethics", "Stakeholder management", "Vitality criterion"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Alexander Brink", "ex:email": "alexander.brink@uni-bayreuth.de"}, {"ex:name": "Johannes Eurich", "ex:email": "johannes.eurich@dwi.uni-heidelberg.de"}]}, {"ex:issue": "1", "ex:volume": "91", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "Do Markets Crowd Out Virtues? An Aristotelian Framework", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-009-0072-6", "ex:pages": "1-19", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2010", "ex:keyword": ["Aristotle", "Capitalism", "Competition", "Doux commerce thesis", "Free market", "Market operation", "Self-destruction thesis", "Virtue ethics"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "J. Graafland", "ex:email": "J.J.Graafland@uvt.nl"}]}, {"ex:issue": "2", "ex:volume": "85", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "The Effects of Proximity and Empathy on Ethical Decision-Making: An Exploratory Investigation", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-008-9765-5", "ex:pages": "201-226", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2009", "ex:keyword": ["Empathy", "Ethical decision-making process", "Magnitude of consequences", "Moral evaluations", "Moral intensity", "Proximity"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Jennifer Mencl", "ex:email": "jmencl@d.umn.edu"}, {"ex:name": "Douglas May", "ex:email": "drmay@ku.edu"}]}, {"ex:issue": "2", "ex:volume": "88", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "Fair Trade in Mexico and Abroad: An Alternative to the Walmartopia?", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-009-0287-6", "ex:pages": "301-317", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2009", "ex:keyword": ["Fair trade", "Mexico", "Globalization", "Coffee"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Jesús Alvarado", "ex:email": "jalvarad@prodigy.net.mx"}]}, {"ex:issue": "1", "ex:volume": "88", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "The Role of NGOs in CSR: Mutual Perceptions Among Stakeholders", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.