arranted to develop a clearer understanding of the linkage between ethical judgment and intention to act in an ethical manner. These findings have implications for global firms, particularly regarding codes of conduct and ethics training. Copyright Springer Science+Business Media B.V. 2007", "ex:volume": "71", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "The Ethical Decision Making of Men and Women Executives in International Business Situations", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-006-9129-y", "ex:pages": "125-134", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2007", "ex:keyword": ["Ethics", "Gender", "Sex", "U.s.", "Spain"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Sean Valentine", "ex:email": "Valentin@uwyo.edu"}, {"ex:name": "Terri Rittenburg"}]}, {"ex:issue": "2", "ex:volume": "86", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "Google in China: A Manager-Friendly Heuristic Model for Resolving Cross-Cultural Ethical Conflicts", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-008-9840-y", "ex:pages": "143-157", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2009", "ex:keyword": ["Cross-cultural ethics", "China", "Decision tree", "International questionable practices", "Google"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "J. Hamilton"}, {"ex:name": "Stephen Knouse"}, {"ex:name": "Vanessa Hill", "ex:email": "vanessa.hill@louisiana.edu"}]}, {"ex:issue": "1", "ex:volume": "88", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "Is There Any Change in the Public Service Values of Different Generations of Public Administrators? The Case of Turkish Governors and District Governors", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-009-0111-3", "ex:pages": "137-156", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2009", "ex:keyword": ["Democratic values", "Ethical values", "New public management", "Professional values", "Public service values", "Turkish governors and district governors"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Ugur Omurgonulsen", "ex:email": "omur@hacettepe.edu.tr"}, {"ex:name": "M. Oktem", "ex:email": "kemalok@