ermore, it is argued that views of (human) agency and the moral subject should be made explicit in such a theory. Copyright Springer Science+Business Media, Inc. 2006", "ex:volume": "68", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "The Autonomy of the Contracting Partners: An Argument for Heuristic Contractarian Business Ethics", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-006-9018-4", "ex:pages": "347-361", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2006", "ex:keyword": ["Autonomy", "Contract theory", "Contractarian business ethics", "Exit option", "Isct"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Gjalt Graaf", "ex:email": "g.de.graaf@fsw.vu.nl"}]}, {"ex:issue": "2", "ex:volume": "89", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "An Investigation of the Effects of Corporate Ethical Values on Employee Commitment and Performance: Examining the Moderating Role of Perceived Fairness", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-008-9997-4", "ex:pages": "251-260", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2009", "ex:keyword": ["Corporate ethical values", "Ethics", "Job performance", "Commitment", "Organizational fairness"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Dheeraj Sharma", "ex:email": "dsharma@athabascau.ca"}, {"ex:name": "Shaheen Borna", "ex:email": "sborna@bsu.edu"}, {"ex:name": "James Stearns", "ex:email": "stearnjm@muohio.edu"}]}, {"ex:issue": "2", "ex:volume": "85", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "CSR Implementation: Developing the Capacity for Collective Action", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-008-9737-9", "ex:pages": "463-477", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2009", "ex:keyword": ["Capacity development", "Corporate social responsibility implementation", "Collective action", "Corporate citizenship", "Enabling environment", "Collaborative capacity", "Organizational capacity"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Dasaratha Rama", "ex:email": "ramad@fiu.edu"}, {"ex:name": "Bernard Milano"}, {"ex:name": "Silvia Salas"}, {"ex:name": "Che-Hung Liu"}]}, {"ex:is