kely to engage in that unethical behavior. Attitude at Time 1 predicted only Factor Abuse Resources for Propensity at Time 2. Propensity at Time 1 was significantly related to Propensity at Time 2. Attitude at Time 1, Propensity at Time 1, and Propensity at Time 2 had achieved configural and metric measurement invariance across major (business vs. psychology). Thus, researchers may have confidence in using these measures in future research. Copyright Springer 2006", "ex:volume": "69", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "Attitude Toward and Propensity to Engage in Unethical Behavior: Measurement Invariance across Major among University Students", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-006-9069-6", "ex:pages": "77-93", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2006", "ex:keyword": ["Attitude toward unethical behavior", "Propensity to engage in unethical behavior", "Measurement invariance", "University students", "Business", "Psychology"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Yuh-Jia Chen", "ex:email": "ychen@mtsu.edu"}, {"ex:name": "Thomas Tang", "ex:email": "ttang@mtsu.edu"}]}, {"ex:issue": "1", "ex:volume": "88", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "Putting Ethics on the Agenda for Real Estate Agents", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-009-0099-8", "ex:pages": "65-82", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2009", "ex:keyword": ["Real estate agents", "Professional ethics", "Law and ethics", "Role ethics", "Collective self-criticism", "Ethical climate development", "Empirical business ethics"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Johannes Brinkmann", "ex:email": "johannes.brinkmann@bi.no"}]}, {"ex:issue": "4", "ex:volume": "90", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "Strategic Risk-Taking Propensity: The Role of Ethical Climate and Marketing Output Control", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-009-0063-7", "ex:pages": "593-606", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2009", "ex:keyword": ["Risk", "Risk-taking propensity", "Ethical climate", "Long-term orientation", "Output control", "Publicly traded", "Privately held"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Amit Saini", "ex:email": "asaini2@unl.edu"}, {"ex:name": "Kelly Martin", "ex:email": "Kelly.Martin@business.colostate.edu"}]}, {"ex:issue": "1", "ex:volume": "85", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "Implementing Supplier Codes of Conduct in Global Supply Chains: Process Explanations from Theoretic and Empirical Perspectives", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-008-9750-z", "ex:pages": "77-92", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2009", "ex:keyword": ["Supplier codes of conduct", "Interorganizational governance", "Transaction cost economics", "Structural equation model", "Mediating process"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Bin Jiang", "ex:email": "bjiang@depaul.edu"}]}, {"ex:issue": "1", "ex:volume": "66", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "Responsible Leadership in a Stakeholder Society – A Relational Perspective", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-006-9047-z", "ex:pages": "99-115", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2006", "ex:keyword": ["Responsible leadership", "Leadership", "Stake- holder theory", "Leadership roles", "Relational intelligence"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Thomas Maak", "ex:email": "thomas.maak@unisg.ch"}, {"ex:name": "Nicola M. Pless"}]}, {"ex:issue": "3", "ex:abstract": "Lapses in ethical conduct by those in corporate and public authority worldwide have given business researchers and practitioners alike cause to re-examine the antecedents to personal ethical values. We explore the relationship between ethical values and an individualâ€™s long-term orientation or LTO, defined as the degree to which one plans for and considers the future, as well as values traditions of the past. Our study also examines the role of work ethic and conservative attitudes in the formation of a personâ€™s long-term orientation and consequent ethical beliefs. Empirically testing these hypothesized relationships using data from 292 subjects, we find that long-term perspectives on tradition and planning indeed engender higher levels of ethical values. The results also support work ethicâ€™s role in fostering tradition and planning, as well as conservatismâ€™s positive association with planning. Additionally, we report how tradition and planning mediate the influence of conservatism and work ethic on the formation of ethical values. Limitations of the study and future research directions, as well as implications for business managers and academics, are also discussed. Copyright Springer Science+Business Media, Inc. 2007", "ex:volume": "71", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "Ethical Values and Long-term Orientation", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-006-9138-x", "ex:pages": "261-274", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2007", "ex:keyword": ["Time orientation", "Planning", "Tradition", "Formation of ethical beliefs", "Measurement"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Jennifer Nevins"}, {"ex:name": "William Bearden"}, {"ex:name": "Bruce Money", "ex:email": "moneyb@byu.edu"}]}, {"ex:issue": "3", "ex:volume": "81", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "Corporate Governance and Ethics: A Feminist Perspective", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-007-9539-5", "ex:pages": "665-678", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2008", "ex:keyword": ["Corporate governance", "Ethical theories", "Feminist ethics"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Silke Machold", "ex:email": "S.Machold@wlv.ac.uk"}, {"ex:name": "Pervaiz Ahmed"}, {"ex:name": "Stuart Farquhar"}]}, {"ex:issue": "4", "ex:volume": "82", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "How Can a Ratings-based Method for Assessing Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) Provide an Incentive to Firms Excluded from Socially Responsible Investment Indices to Invest in CSR?", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-007-9600-4", "ex:pages": "899-905", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2008",