nd deal with these dilemmas. The research is based on interviews with seven entrepreneurs in established service-oriented ventures, which gave rise to 26 dilemmas. These dilemmas were analyzed by making use of the Synergy Star technique, which is introduced here as a tool that is useful in defining any dilemma, isolating the ethical component, and resolving the dilemma in a way that is congruent with the entrepreneurâ€™s personal world-view. Copyright Springer Science+Business Media, Inc. 2007", "ex:volume": "71", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "How Entrepreneurs Deal with Ethical Challenges â€“ An Application of the Business Ethics Synergy Star Technique", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-006-9148-8", "ex:pages": "411-423", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2007", "ex:keyword": ["Entrepreneur", "Ethics", "Synergy star", "Bess", "Ethical dilemma"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "David Robinson", "ex:email": "da.robinson@qut.edu.au"}, {"ex:name": "Per Davidsson"}, {"ex:name": "Hennie Mescht"}, {"ex:name": "Philip Court"}]}, {"ex:issue": "2", "ex:volume": "91", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "Ethical Attitudes of Accounting Practitioners: Are Rank and Ethical Attitudes Related?", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-009-0076-2", "ex:pages": "183-194", "ex:year": "", "ex:date": "2010", "ex:keyword": ["Ethical attitudes", "Accounting practitioners", "Inverse rank-ethical beliefs", "Auditors", "Ethics"], "ex:creator": [{"ex:name": "Stephen Conroy", "ex:email": "sconroy@sandiego.edu"}, {"ex:name": "Tisha Emerson", "ex:email": "Tisha_Nakao@baylor.edu"}, {"ex:name": "Frank Pons", "ex:email": "Frank.Pons@fsa.ulaval.ca"}]}, {"ex:issue": "4", "ex:volume": "89", "ex:source": "Journal of Business Ethics", "ex:title": "The Contribution of Environmental and Social Standards Towards Ensuring Legitimacy in Supply Chain Governance", "ex:url": "http://hdl.handle.net/10.1007/s10551-008-0013-9", "ex:pages": "509-523", "ex:y